column5: lol, send me some pics. I would like to add a bunch   Thanks Leechman!
Great Job Dan I have a few pics laying around from 2010.
Like the title says Dan B set up a website for the fish a thon go have a look and get that hit counter turning  http://www.fish-a-thon.com/
Don't be cruel about the look, I need to spend A LOT more time on it lol
You've done a great job so far.

Thats awesome.  A very worthy cause. This last fish-a-thon was my first but I plan to get a few friends involved next year.  It is a good day, with a bucn of good guys (for the most part), for a worthy cause.  Ryan and Dan and many others put alot of work in behind teh scenes to make it happen. Thanks guys!!  BF
Looks just fine to me Dan we haven't even discussed a date yet and I'm already looking forward to it.
Awesome Job Dan So far so good
Great stuff, guys!!  Really looking forward to making this year's Fish-A-Thon, the best yet!!  I know Ryan is really busy right now, but, we'll all get the ball rolling soon.  Fantastic Dan!

it was a great time out there for sure. I need to figure out what I'm going to use for a boat this year sold off the 14ft I had so now just the 16 and my electric troling motor just doesn't seem to cut it on that boat for some reason. Just might have to find me antother small boat or better trolling equipment

hey guys, I read my name on the site, thanks but it's not needed to have me as a sponsor. however, if I win the current contest from TJ and Dave, I will donate the $200 gift from Dave to the event (I may take a lure or two though, LOL). If I win from TJ, forget it, I want an OFC summer and winter hat.  The rest can go to the event (if there is anything left   ) Cheers and I hope the site get's a lot of hit's and can raise some cash at the same time.  Cheers. Geoff
Ryan - Send Dave an email quick
i might go. depends really how things are played out.

fine with me.  I even said it on his facebook contest; here's what I said; "Congrats to you Shaun Quinn. I would have been happy with a signed casting for the cure hat and the $200 go to the charity."

I still get a chuckle out of that photo of Juli, myself and the boys...Juli is about 5'2", but is standing at the bottom on a slope...makes me look about 6'8", instead of the 6'2" or so that I really am. By the way, nice gesture Geoff!!
Hey, it was worth it if I won.  I don't need the stuff Frank.
I added a "like" button for all the Facebook guys and also redid the page. Feel free to "like" it
I checked it out Dan.... looks awesome dude
I liked it! I want to make it this year.

Saw the post on the WFN site -- left a comment there, but I just wanted to say it's a great start to getting the word out about a truly worthy cause. It looks like a great event and I look forward to finding out more about it as the site comes together.  Thanks!
Definately a worthy cause, good work so far on the site.  I couldn't make it last year but hope to this year.
Just hit the 1000 visitor mark
Yikes!...thats a horrible pic of me..less the big box of goodies that is  Let me know and if you want ill forward you a better pic of myself from that day...lol
Wow great work Dan.... Love the new look and feel 1020 just now
